{"ts":"2026-07-21T10:31:19.916Z","sessionId":"s_f0f4e55d","event":"task_complete","detail":"Phase 2 complete: the full C++ engine (~3,500 LOC). Arena-backed Tensor<T>, tape autograd, ten ops with hand-derived backwards (matmul, matmul_bt, add, rmsnorm, rope, softmax_causal, silu, swiglu, embedding, fused cross_entropy), fused causal MHA with RoPE, pre-norm block stack with weight-tied lm_head, AdamW + global-norm clipping, temperature/top-k/top-p sampler, minimal JSON reader, mmap-able .csllm checkpoints, and an incremental KV-cache decode path. pybind11 surface releases the GIL and exposes a per-op gradcheck harness plus an f64 Model. Verified: 83 tests, 0 compiler warnings, ruff clean; forwards match NumPy oracles to 1e-11; all backwards match double-precision finite differences (~2e-10 vs gradients of magnitude 1, with harness sensitivity confirmed); overfit-one-batch 2.803 -> 0.000043 reproducing all target tokens; 12M config runs at 0.28 s/step with init loss 8.337 > ln(4096)=8.318.","meta":{"taskId":"t_872cf28d","updatedFiles":["design","phase","memory"]}}
{"ts":"2026-07-21T10:37:16.854Z","sessionId":"s_f0f4e55d","event":"task_begin","detail":"Phase 3: byte-level BPE tokenizer (trainer + encode/decode, lossless UTF-8 round-trip), TinyShakespeare download and uint16 binarization with a batch sampler, and the Python training loop driving the C++ backend (AdamW, cosine schedule with warmup, grad clipping, validation, sampling, resumable .csllm checkpoints). Validate on configs/debug.json, then run the real 12M training.","meta":{"taskId":"t_d43610d8"}}
{"ts":"2026-07-21T11:06:29.908Z","sessionId":"s_f0f4e55d","event":"file_written","detail":"Wrote memory.md (6424 bytes)","meta":{"key":"memory","summary":"Running knowledge base: Phases 1-3 complete; a trained 12M model exists (1.41 nats/char); environment, engine, and training gotchas for future agents."}}
{"ts":"2026-07-21T11:06:53.240Z","sessionId":"s_f0f4e55d","event":"file_written","detail":"Wrote phase.md (3715 bytes)","meta":{"key":"phase","summary":"Phases 1-3 complete with a trained 12M model; awaiting user approval to begin Phase 4 (FastAPI SSE gateway)."}}
{"ts":"2026-07-21T11:07:17.586Z","sessionId":"s_f0f4e55d","event":"task_complete","detail":"Phase 3 complete: byte-level BPE tokenizer with incremental merge training (3,840 merges over 1.1MB in 1.9s, lossless round-trip on emoji/CJK/control bytes/BMP fuzz), TinyShakespeare download + uint16 binarization (344,120 tokens @ 3.24 chars/token), the training loop (AdamW, cosine+warmup, grad clipping, eval, best-val checkpointing, sampling, --resume), and train/sample.py with UTF-8-boundary streaming. Added 51 tests (134 total), ruff clean, Makefile targets. Trained the 12M model in 11.9 min: best val 4.2996/token at step 1000 = 1.41 nats/char, 2.03 bits/char, perplexity 80.5, generating coherent Shakespearean dialogue. Key finding: matching the cosine schedule to the actual run length (1500 vs 3000 steps) improved val loss 3.8% in half the wall-clock, because the 3000-step run stranded its best checkpoint mid-schedule at near-maximum LR.","meta":{"taskId":"t_d43610d8","updatedFiles":["phase","memory"]}}
{"ts":"2026-07-21T11:10:22.334Z","sessionId":"s_f0f4e55d","event":"task_begin","detail":"Phase 4: FastAPI gateway — lifespan model+tokenizer load, Pydantic-validated /generate with SSE streaming, per-request GenerationSession with private KV cache, asyncio.to_thread dispatch, concurrency semaphore, UTF-8 boundary buffering, client-disconnect abort, /health. Also fix a prefill/step off-by-one that re-processes the last prompt token.","meta":{"taskId":"t_0133dcfd"}}
{"ts":"2026-07-21T11:18:18.631Z","sessionId":"s_f0f4e55d","event":"file_written","detail":"Wrote memory.md (6914 bytes)","meta":{"key":"memory","summary":"Running knowledge base: all four phases complete — C++ engine, trained 12M model, and a live SSE gateway; plus the environment/engine/training/serving gotchas future agents need."}}
{"ts":"2026-07-21T11:18:41.945Z","sessionId":"s_f0f4e55d","event":"file_written","detail":"Wrote phase.md (3483 bytes)","meta":{"key":"phase","summary":"All four phases complete: C++ engine, trained 12M model, and a live SSE gateway (164 tests). Remaining work is backlog only."}}
{"ts":"2026-07-21T11:18:51.693Z","sessionId":"s_f0f4e55d","event":"task_complete","detail":"Phase 4 complete: FastAPI gateway with lifespan model+tokenizer load, Pydantic v2 validated /generate (SSE streaming and non-streaming JSON), /health, per-request GenerationSession with private KV cache, asyncio.to_thread dispatch over GIL-releasing bindings, concurrency semaphore with timeout to 503, UTF-8 boundary buffering, and client-disconnect abort. Added 27 gateway tests (164 total), ruff clean, 0 C++ warnings. Also found and fixed a latent generation bug: prefill() consumes the entire prompt, so step(prompt[-1]) fed the prompt's last token twice and generated from a corrupted context (invisible in loss metrics; it made 'KING RICHARD:\\n' become a duplicated newline so the model started a new speaker). Added GenerationSession::sample_last() working on a scratch copy, fixed train/train.py and train/sample.py, and added three regression tests. Verified live against the trained 12M model: TTFT 19 ms, ~565 tok/s, 4 concurrent streams at 1.95x one stream's wall-clock, disconnect frees the slot, all malformed requests 422.","meta":{"taskId":"t_0133dcfd","updatedFiles":["phase","memory"]}}
{"ts":"2026-07-21T11:37:36.971Z","sessionId":"s_f0f4e55d","event":"task_begin","detail":"CSLLM 2.0 Phase 1: dataset plugin system (DatasetPlugin ABC, extension-keyed registry, built-in .txt/.jsonl/.csv readers), optional special-token support in the BPE tokenizer for multi-document corpora, prepare_dataset() streaming through the registry, and the safetensors export pipeline (model.safetensors + tokenizer.json + config.json) with no torch dependency.","meta":{"taskId":"t_09e89c12"}}
