{"ts":"2026-07-21T17:24:57.655Z","sessionId":"s_f0f4e55d","event":"task_complete","detail":"CSLLM 2.0 Phase 2 complete. C++: added opt-in attention capture to GenerationSession (last_attention() -> [n_layer, n_head, keys]), bound the previously-unbound decode(), and refactored Sampler so sample() is built on a new distribution() — one filtering implementation so a UI chart cannot drift from the real sampler; sample() is now non-mutating. Python: train.py gained --emit-jsonl/--run-id while staying standalone; gateway/telemetry.py implements TrainingSupervisor (subprocess, JSONL vs log discrimination, bounded per-subscriber queues where newest always wins so terminal events are never lost, history replay, runs/<id> artifacts); gateway/versioning.py implements a fingerprinted idempotent ConfigStore; the gateway was split into routes/{inference,training,config,datasets}.py with new /train/{start,stop,status}, WS /ws/train, /configure_model, /configs, /export, /datasets endpoints. Added 56 tests (280 total), ruff clean, 0 compiler warnings. Verified live: attention matches an independent NumPy recomputation to 2.5e-07; a real 60-step run streamed 60 loss points, 22 log lines and 2 evals over WebSocket; concurrent start 409s; mid-flight stop returns -15. Fixed two real bugs found by testing: @dataclass made _Subscriber unhashable (needs eq=False), and stop() returned before the output pump finalised returncode, leaving status() reporting running=True — caught only by the live run, not the unit test.","meta":{"taskId":"t_b3b36d96","updatedFiles":["phase","memory"]}}
{"ts":"2026-07-21T17:28:27.191Z","sessionId":"s_f0f4e55d","event":"task_begin","detail":"CSLLM 2.0 Phase 3: inspection endpoints (/tokenize, /embeddings, /inspect/next_token reusing the C++ filtered_distribution) plus the Vite + React + TypeScript frontend in web/ with TokenizerPanel (token chunks + embedding heatmap) and ProbabilityPanel (temperature/top-k/top-p sliders + live probability chart).","meta":{"taskId":"t_d2a8623c"}}
