{"ts":"2026-07-21T17:59:21.149Z","sessionId":"s_f0f4e55d","event":"file_written","detail":"Wrote phase.md (3893 bytes)","meta":{"key":"phase","summary":"CSLLM 1.0 complete; 2.0 Phases 1-3 complete (datasets/export, telemetry/attention capture, React diagnostics UI); awaiting approval for Phase 4 (R3F attention animation + training dashboard)."}}
{"ts":"2026-07-21T17:59:36.898Z","sessionId":"s_f0f4e55d","event":"task_complete","detail":"CSLLM 2.0 Phase 3 complete. Backend: /tokenize (byte spans + partial-UTF-8 flags), /embeddings (zero-copy tok_emb rows + SVD/PCA to 3D), /inspect/next_token (raw softmax plus the C++ filtered_distribution, ranked by max(raw, filtered) so excluded-but-likely tokens stay visible). Frontend: web/ Vite + React + TypeScript with TokenizerPanel, EmbeddingHeatmap (canvas, diverging ramp), ProbabilityPanel with Chart.js grouped bars and a table view, hash-addressable tabs, light/dark, request cancellation. Added 25 backend + 30 frontend tests (305 Python total), ruff clean, tsc clean, 0 compiler warnings. Followed the dataviz skill: ran validate_palette.js (blue/orange pass every gate both modes) and verified diverging-arm lightness monotonicity computationally. Visual verification in headless Chrome caught three bugs no test did: (1) API_BASE hard-coded to /api, which only exists behind the Vite dev proxy, so every call in the built app hit the StaticFiles mount and returned Method Not Allowed; (2) the diverging scale had a neutral POINT rather than a band, so with continuous data every cell got a hue and near-zero never read as neutral; (3) scaling the heatmap to max() put 86% of cells into two near-identical steps, fixed with a p98 robust limit and a stated clip count. Also fixed -0.000 entropy display and windowed the 384-dim heatmap for legibility.","meta":{"taskId":"t_d2a8623c","updatedFiles":["phase","memory"]}}
{"ts":"2026-07-21T18:11:58.657Z","sessionId":"s_f0f4e55d","event":"task_begin","detail":"CSLLM 2.0 Phase 4: WS /ws/inspect streaming per-token metadata plus binary Float32Array attention frames with layer/head filtering; React Three Fiber TransformerGraph animating real captured attention; TrainingDashboard subscribing to /ws/train with loss curves, log console and start/stop controls; enable the two disabled tabs.","meta":{"taskId":"t_d0695b69"}}
{"ts":"2026-07-21T18:38:11.597Z","sessionId":"s_f0f4e55d","event":"file_written","detail":"Wrote memory.md (7186 bytes)","meta":{"key":"memory","summary":"Running knowledge base: CSLLM 1.0 and 2.0 both complete — C++ engine, trained model, gateway, and full React diagnostics UI; all environment, engine, training, serving and frontend gotchas."}}
{"ts":"2026-07-21T18:38:35.376Z","sessionId":"s_f0f4e55d","event":"file_written","detail":"Wrote phase.md (3200 bytes)","meta":{"key":"phase","summary":"All phases of CSLLM 1.0 and 2.0 are complete; remaining work is backlog only."}}
{"ts":"2026-07-21T18:38:51.912Z","sessionId":"s_f0f4e55d","event":"task_complete","detail":"CSLLM 2.0 Phase 4 complete, finishing the project. Added WS /ws/inspect streaming a JSON metadata frame followed by a binary Float32Array attention frame per token, with layer/head filtering applied before serialisation (the full block is ~36 KB/token at full context, unusable as JSON); the loop uses decode() rather than step() so each frame pairs the attention actually used with the distribution the token was drawn from. Extracted gateway/inspection.py so the REST and WS surfaces share one candidate computation. Frontend: useInspectStream (pairs JSON and binary frames via a single pending slot, since frames are strictly ordered), useTrainingStream (replayed history, bounded logs), TransformerGraph in React Three Fiber (lazy-loaded, adaptive camera framing, height AND colour both encoding attention so the reading survives greyscale, sequential one-hue ramp since attention has magnitude without polarity), AttentionPanel, LossChart/Sparkline (train and val on one axis; LR and grad-norm in separate charts rather than a second y-axis), and TrainingDashboard with start/stop. Enabled both tabs. Added 20 backend + 9 frontend tests (325 Python + 39 frontend total), ruff clean, tsc clean, 0 compiler warnings. Verified by driving the real application over the Chrome DevTools Protocol: clicked Generate and received 16 tokens with 25.9 KB of binary attention in a 6x6x19 block, then started a 300-step training run from the browser that ran to completion (loss 6.24 -> 3.84, best val 3.8373, exit 0, ~102k tok/s). Fixed the 3D camera, which used a fixed distance and left the short wide attention grid stranded in the middle of the canvas.","meta":{"taskId":"t_d0695b69","updatedFiles":["phase","memory"]}}
